y the dock in Toxx.  8 min. respawn I think, if you read a book and do it for a few hours you'll get the faction you need.  There are a couple of mobs in Paineel that work too but I think the Toxx necro is the best way. <p><BR>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131249>Aalek</a>
<BR>
60 Crusader
<BR>
Reign in Power
<BR>
Torvonnilous</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utigrus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tigrus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/14/02 1:28:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3460.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What can i do to increase erudin factions?</span><hr size=1> I dont believe the guards are on the same faction as the quest NPC's for the epic.  You need to con indifferent to Reklon Gnallen, I'm not sure what quest raises his faction, I believe it is peacekeeper faction though.  You also need to get your Deepwater Knight faction up which you can do by killing the necro by the docks in Toxx over and over.  Its name is Elial Brook.  There are also 2 npcs in paineel that give the DW knights faction named Azzar Habbib and Noclin Saah.  If you kill these guys enough you will get good faction with the Deepwater knights and this will allow you to do the turn in in Plane of Air.  I havent heard of anyone having problems with Reklon's faction not being indifferent.<br>
<br>
EDIT: When I did it, i would run between paineel and toxx killing all three of them, so it wasnt as boring.  And also Keeper of the Tombs gives DW faction increase. <p>Baron <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=10979">Tigrus</a><br>
Crusader of Mithaniel Marr<br>
Proud Officer of Robble<br>
Prexus Server</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utigrus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tigrus</A> at: 4/14/02 1:30:01 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalidin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balidin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 307<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/14/02 2:12:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3460.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What can i do to increase erudin factions?</span><hr size=1> If you ever plan to go to the Hole, do this:<br>
<br>
Kill kobolds. About 2000 to 3000 should do what you need. (and overkill, actually-but best to be safe)<br>
<br>
Buy your Hole key, it's available near the bank.<br>
<br>
Kill those heretics. They were so demanding of you when you were trying to convince them to like you, they deserve it. <p><font><font size=3><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45984>Balidin</a>,</font> The Evilbasher</b><BR><font color=red><i>Cavalier of Mithaniel</i><BR><font color=white>Apprentice of the Healing Arts of Rodcet Nife</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueumerin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eumerin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 189<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/15/02 9:19:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3460.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What can i do to increase erudin factions?</span><hr size=1> A guide to Erudite factions<br>
<br>
There are a few different factions within Erudin.  The key factions are the following:<br>
<br>
Peacekeepers of Erudin - Temple of Divine Light<br>
Deepwater Knights - Temple of Prexus<br>
Highguard of Erudin - the local guards<br>
Council of Erudin - I *believe* this is the heads of the intelli-caster guilds, although I'm not certain.<br>
Craftkeepers - Enchanters guild<br>
Crimson Hands - Wizards guild (also very similar to a former evil guild on my server - Order of the Crimson Hands <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   )<br>
Gatecallers - Magicians guild<br>
Citizens of Erudin (I *think* that's the name - its been a while) - Probably random citizen faction.  Almost useless for most players.<br>
<br>
Peacekeeper faction can ONLY be raised by doing either Peacekeeper or Kejek quests (the latter are found in the Kejek village in Stonebrunt).  There is no mob you can kill to raise this faction, and until The Warrens went live, it was impossible for those who did not start out with high enough faction to raise it.<br>
Deepwater Knight faction can be raised by killing the necro at the docks in Toxulia, killing other heretics, or turning in kobold molars at the Temple of Prexus.<br>
Highguard faction can be raised in a variety of ways.  iirc, these include killing Kerrans (NOT Kejek, which will screw up your Peacekeeper faction in a big way) and kobolds.  You might be able to kill heretics (memory is shaky on this one).<br>
Highcouncil faction can be raised by killing Kerrans.<br>
Intelli-caster factions - I *think* these can be raised by killing heretics, although I'm not sure.<br>
Citizens of Erudin - to the best of my knowledge, the only way of raising this faction is by handing Innoruuk's Kiss to whatsername in the Library of Erudin for the Vasty Deep Water.  There is no known reason for anyone to need this faction, however.<br>
 <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=96807 target="web">Eumerin Paxodus</a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulorddenman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lord Denman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/15/02 11:02:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3460.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What can i do to increase erudin factions?</span><hr size=1> Go to Lavastorm mountain.  On top of a hill, there is a goblin camp, with a heretic necromancer.  Kill her everytime you go to and from Sol A or Sol B.  She will increase your Erudite faction nicely.<br>
<br>
Denman Cinqueports<br>
The Knights of the Crystal Rose<br>
E'ci <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udelgardblackburn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DelgardBlackburn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 9:26:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3460.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What can i do to increase erudin factions?</span><hr size=1> When you killing Elia (sp?) Brooks the Necro near the Docks in Tox. Take his bones and turn them into the quest giver (sorry forget the name In the caster guilds, again off hand don't remember wich but think it was gatecallers) this raises most of all the Erudin factions. Only Faction that I have found that is hard to get is Quellious. Only way I have found is the quest in Stonebrunt.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ushehabaldean.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shehab al dean</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arabian Crusader</span><br>  Posts: 612<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 8:50:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3460.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://forzaq8.net/everquest/personal.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What can i do to increase erudin factions?</span><hr size=1> the bones goes to the magican guild master ( gatekeepers ) <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usinianadartanian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Siniana Dartanian</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/02 7:32:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3460.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.shinysteel.com/images/sini_face.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What can i do to increase erudin factions?</span><hr size=1> Also, there is a guy near the entrance to the field in Paineel you can kill (the newbie quest guy named ----?) and he respawns within about 5 minutes. I killed him 20 times and went from indiff to amiable.<br>
<br>
Just a thought. <p><center><img src="http://www.shinysteel.com/images/sini.gif " </center>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umrgoodkin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mr Goodkin </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/02 6:27:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3460.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Answer is attached my friend.</span><hr size=1> You guys are funny.  Being on Firiona Vie, most of us visit warrens at one time or another.  It is a gold mine from 7-20 for platinum, exp and faction.<br>
<br>
Regarding faction, by killing Kobolds either in Tox or in Warrens, you get faction up with Erudite guards and Heretics.  There are halfling druids running around Paineel on our server from the time spent in the Warrens.<br>
<br>
Now, if you seek faction with the Paladins of the Deepwater, you turn in molars (no drop except on my server) to Tiam in courtyard of that guild.  I went from apprehensive to amiable to now warm in 2 levels.  Probably about 50 molars.  Of course, this drops you Heretic faction but who cares.<br>
<br>
So, whether it is the guards or Deepwater Paladin guild, Kobalds and their molars (that drop off even the runts) will get you those 2 faction hits.  <br>
<br>
Good luck. <p>May Brell shine the light in your eyes ~ <BR> Goody <BR> Firiona Vie</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showPrevMessage?topicID=3460.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showNextMessage?topicID=3460.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3460.topic&index=9><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.emailToFriend?topicID=3460.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.threadControl?topicID=3460.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3460.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3460.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="paladinsofnorrathgeneral">General<option value="paladinsofnorrathfrm14">Norrath Classic 